value.value: The antennal muscle that arises anterolaterally on the scape and inserts medially on the proximal part of the pedicel.
The tergite that is located medially on the tergum.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesobasalare.
The coxal foramen that is on the mesopectus.
The leg muscle that inserts on the mesocoxa.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesofurca.

The area that is well sclerotised, composes the lateral part of the mesophragma and is continuous with the dorsal and ventral mesopostnotal flanges, is connected distally with the subalare and ventrally bears the mesopostnotal apodeme.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesolaterophragma.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesonotum.
The intersegmental membrane that is located between the mesopectus and the pronotum.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesophragma.
The second abdominal sternal muscle that arises from the metapleuron.
The propodeal muscle that arises from the metapleuron.
The area that is located proximoventrally on the mandible, is projected posteriorly and bears posteroventrally oriented rows of spines.
The area that extends along the posterior margin of the mesoscutellum and is delimited anteriorly by the posterior mesoscutellar sulcus.
The ridge that is unpaired, vertical, is located in the dorsoventral midline of the frons and corresponds to the site of origin of the posterior fronto-labral muscles.

The antennal muscle that arises anteriorly from the anterior tentorial arm anteromedially of the site of origin of the anterior tentorio-scapal muscle and inserts medially on the proximal part of the scape.
The projection that is located distomedially on the parossiculus and is continuous with the volsellar ridge.
The carina that delimits the spiracular furrow medially.
The anterior thoracic spiracle occlusor muscle that originates from the prepectus and inserts on the mesothoracic spiracle.
The area that is horizontal and located ventrally on the prepectus.
The carina that divides the prepectus for the vertical lateral portion and the horizontal, ventral prepectal shelf.
The mesobasalar muscle that arises from the prepectus.
The postoccipital muscle that arises from the propleural arm.
The procoxal muscle that originates from the propleural arm.
The area that is located on the conjunctiva and invaginated.
The area that is located medially on the dorsellum and bears the metanotal flange.
The rim that surrounds the occipital foramen.
The sulcus that extends between the malar sulcus and the occipital foramen.
The antennal muscle that arises medially from the proximal parts of the dorsal and anterior tentorial arms and is inserted posteriorly (dorsally) on the proximal part of the scape.
The ovipositor muscle that arises medially from the posterodorsal part of female T9 and inserts on the median bridge of the second valvifers.
The stipito-palpal muscle that arises medially on the proximal part of the stipes and inserts posteroproximally on the first maxillary palpal segment.
The ovipositor muscle that arises posteroventrally from the second valvifer and inserts on the processus musculares of the second valvula.
The area that is posterior and set of from the mesoscutellum by a transverse line.
The pronoto-laterocervical muscle that originates from the pronotum posterior to the anterior pronoto-laterocervical muscle and inserts on the laterocervical apodeme.
The paired process that is located posteriorly on the dorsal surface of the mesoscutellum.
The metacoxal muscle that arises from the metanotum posterior to the site of origin of the anterior metanoto-metacoxal muscle.
The flange that is located on the frontal carina and obscures the antennal foramen.
The area that is located between the epistomal sulcus and the frontal line .
The line that delimits dorsally the scrobal depression.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the vertex and the dorsal area of the upper face dorsal to the frontofacial ridge.

The bar that extends between each eye ventral (anterior) to the anterior ocellus and dorsal (posterior) to the antennal formamina and laterally terminates at the juncture of the supraorbital trabecula and preorbital trabecula.
The line that delimits dorsally the frontal triangle.
The area that is located laterally of the propodeal spiracle and is delimited anterolaterally by the metapleural sulcus.
The area that is located arond the anal opening posterior to the epipygium and hypopygium.
The thoracic muscle that inserts on the mesosubalare.
The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 2.
The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 3.
The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 4.
The mediosternite that is located on abdominal sternum 5.
